Diversity index

Source: R/diversityFunctions.R
divLevel.Rd

calculate a sublist of diversity indices on gene segments.

Usage

divLevel(
  x,
  index = c("shannon", "simpson", "invsimpson"),
  level = c("VJ", "V", "J"),
  norm = TRUE,
  base = exp(1)
)

Arguments

x

an object of class [RepSeqExperiment]

index

character, the diversity index to calculate. Should be one of "chaowor","shannon","invsimpson","simpson" or "gini".

level

character, the level of the repertoire to estimate. Should be one of "V", "J" or "VJ".

norm

boolean, whether to compute the normalized diversity index, which divides the computed value by the log(S), S being the number of observed species in the repetoire. Default is TRUE.

base

a positive or complex number, the base with respect to which logarithms are computed. Default is e=exp(1).

Value

a data.table

Details

function computes the diversity indices for level VJ, V or J only.

Examples


data(RepSeqData)

divLevel(x = RepSeqData, index = "shannon", level = "V", norm = TRUE)
